<L>__{interior slave shack night}
<A>__{slaves are crammed into the shack literally on top of each other as they try to sleep. some lay, some sit up. packed in like cattle, there is barely room to move let alone draw a deep, clean breath. there is a real risk of suffocating in the mass. some cough and wheeze.}
<B>__{a child cries...}
<A>__{among them is solomon who must believe at this point that his life has reached its very lowest pointerior the odds of survival are slight, let alone the chance of actually ever returning to his family. this clearly weighs on him as he struggles to find anything like comfortable space in the pen.}
